uk.ac.ebi.pride.utilities.data.controller.impl.ControllerImpl

Class AbstractDataAccessController

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ebi.pride.utilities.data.controller.impl.ControllerImpl.AbstractDataAccessController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MetaDataAccess, MzGraphDataAccess, PeptideDataAccess, ProteinDataAccess, ProteinGroupDataAccess, QuantDataAccess, DataAccessController
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CachedDataAccessController

    public abstract class AbstractDataAccessController
extends Object
implements DataAccessController
    AbstractDataAccessController provides an abstract implementation of DataAccessController. This is solely based on getting the data directly from data source.

    Author:
    Rui Wang, Yasset Perez-Riverol

      • setInferredProteinGroups

        public final void setInferredProteinGroups(Map<Comparable,Map<Comparable,List<Comparable>>> proteinGroups)
        Description copied from interface: ProteinGroupDataAccess
        This method sets the protein groups calculated by a protein inference.

        After the protein groups are set to "!= null", these protein groups are returned and all other implementation of protein groups are ignored.

        the groups are rebuild by using the mapping PAG_ID -> (Protein_ID -> [Peptide_IDs])

        if the peptide_IDs-list is null, then all peptides are used of the protein (no filtering or all passed filtering)

        Specified by:
        setInferredProteinGroups in interface ProteinGroupDataAccess
        Parameters:
        proteinGroups - A java.lang.Map of protein groups to be set
